This garden pays homage to the musician Gabriel Piern√© (1863-1937). It is dominated by a bronze statue of Marcello Tommasi ‚ÄúCarolina‚Äù (1968), which you can appreciate sitting on the stone benches in the shape of an open book. It stands out from the trellis forming elegant columns and plant arcades at the foot of which magnolias cut into cones blossom in spring. They alternate with clumps of rhododendrons whose decorative virtues are well established here. You will notice that unlike all the gardens of Paris, the ground is not covered with sand, but with a paving of sandstone and granite, on which the shadow of cherry trees with pink flowers takes shape each year at spring. But the largest tree of all, which you will easily recognize, is a catalpa about sixty years old.
